&lt;h2&gt;Alloy is where you belong!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alloy is the AI-powered identity and fraud prevention platform that accelerates onboarding, stops fraud, and scales compliance across the customer lifecycle so financial organizations can grow without limits. More than 900 of the world&#39;s leading financial institutions and fintechs trust Alloy for smarter risk management that drives growth.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Through our values: Be Bold, Go Fast, Collaborate, and Celebrate Our Differences, we are creating a workplace where you can grow, thrive, and belong. See how we’ve been continuously recognized and named one of &lt;u&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.inc.com/profile/alloy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Inc.Magazine’s Best Workplaces&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;, &lt;u&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.forbes.com/companies/alloy/?list=americas-best-startup-employers&amp;amp;sh=55c076453c61&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Forbes America’s Best Startup &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.forbes.com/companies/alloy/?list=americas-best-startup-employers&amp;amp;sh=55c076453c61&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Employers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.americanbanker.com/list/best-places-to-work-in-fintech-2022&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Best Fintech to Work for by American Banker&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, year after year.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Check out our investors and read more about us &lt;span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.alloy.com/about&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Engineering Manager to lead our Developer Experience team within the Connection organization. This team owns Alloy&#39;s external-facing integration surface - the APIs, webhooks, and tooling that developers and partners use to connect with Alloy and build on top of our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will lead a team responsible for the systems and experiences that make Alloy easy to integrate with: our Events API, Outgoing Webhooks Service, partnership data feeds, external developer documentation, and the integrations that power Alloy&#39;s channel partner ecosystem. You will own the technical and strategic vision for how data flows in and out of Alloy at scale, and how external developers experience the platform - from first API call to production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alloy operates in a hybrid-work environment. We look to foster collaboration and community by having our local employees onsite three days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Engineering Manager&#39;s primary responsibility is their team. You will balance three key areas: recruiting and growing great engineers, supporting each person&#39;s development, and partnering with product and stakeholders to ship high-quality, high-impact work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As the Engineering Manager, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and mentor a team of engineers through weekly 1:1s, career conversations, and hands-on technical guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the roadmap and delivery for Alloy&#39;s developer-facing infrastructure — APIs, webhooks, data ingestion, and outbound data flows - ensuring reliability, scalability, and a great developer experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with product, design, partnerships, and customer-facing teams to shape what gets built and why.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive technical strategy for the team&#39;s systems, including API design standards, event delivery guarantees, and integration patterns used by external developers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and improve engineering health using DORA metrics and team-level KPIs; establish release and monitoring standards that keep quality high.&lt;/li&gt;

